MBOMBELA – A violent altercation among Laerskool Bergland pupils, captured on video last year, has recently gone viral on social media. The school has confirmed that the fight had in fact taken place. Deputy principal Ian Evans said grade seven learners were involved. They have since left the school to attend high school. Evans explained that three pupils were involved and that the victim, as seen on the video, had started the fight. He said all three learners were suspended, according to the school’s disciplinary procedures.  